First Scientific Meeting: A convergence of the ways: Science and Business. RAED – IESE -ULPGC

Date: from 8 to 11 June 2017 Place: Fuerteventura, Las Palmas de Gran Canaria

Scientific programme:

Inaugural speech: Serendipity in Science, Sheldom L. Glashow, Nobel Prize in Physics Introduced by Catalina Ruiz, Professor of Physics at the University of La Laguna and winner of the Canary Islands Award for Research.

Round-table discussion:

Economics, politics and business: uncertainties, risks and opportunities; Hisham El Sherif, chairman of Nile Capital Investment; José María Gay, academician of the RAED; Jose Manuel Calavia, academician of the RAED; Nilo García Manchado, entrepreneur; Lorenzo Gascón, economist and academic of the RAED; Frédéric Borràs, academician of the RAED. Chaired by Claudia Arteaga, journalist and lecturer in the politics of communication.

Speech:

The impact of GM food on the alleviating of world hunger Richard Roberts, Nobel Prize in Medicine Introduced by Lluis Serra, Professor of Public Health at ULPGC

Speech:

International cooperation applied to specific, measurable objectives Luis López, thoracic surgeon at SCS, professor at ULPGC and winner of the Canary Islands Award for International Cooperation

Corner of excellence: An excellent opportunity to chat in a relaxed and friendly with some of the guests present at different places around the hotel.

Debate: What use is science to business? Pure vs applied science

Participants:

Sheldom L. Glashow, Nobel Prize in Physics;

Richard Roberts, Nobel Prize in Medicine;

José María Baldasano, King Jaume I Environmental Award;

Sonia Fernández-Vidal, lecturer at UAB and educator;

Juan Ruiz Alzola, professor at ULPGC;

Jaume Armengou, academician of the RAED.

Chaired by: Jordi Marti, academician of the RAED.

Speech:

A history of tenacity: the discovery of the structure of the ribosomes

Speaker:

Ada Yonath, Nobel Prize in Chemistry;

introduced by Cecilia Kindelan, Associate Director of the MBA Programme and Director of the International Exchange Programme of IESE.

Round-table discussion:

Technology and sustainable development

Participants:

Juan Ruiz, professor at ULPGC;

Luis López, Director of International Cooperation at SCS;

Catalina Ruiz, professor at ULL;

Lluís Serra, professor at ULPGC;

Josefa de la Rosa, Director of CUCID ULPGC.

Chaired by: Mari Àngels Calvo, academician of the RAED

Round-table discussion: The world’s new political scene: threats and forecasts

Participants:

Walter Lichem, former ambassador of Austria; Rosalía Arteaga, former president of Ecuador;

Inocencio Arias, former ambassador of Spain;

Ernst Iten, former ambassador Switzerland;

Joaquín Almunia, former European Commissioner.

Dr. Luis Alberto Lacalle, former president of Uruguay.

Chaired by: Claudia Arteaga, journalist and lecturer in the politics of communication

Admission as Numerary Academician: José Ramón Calvo Fernández

Tobacco or health: children do not choose Answering speech: Jordi Martí Pidelaserra

Admission as Honorary Academicians

Sheldon L. Glashow, Nobel Prize in Physics Introduced by Dr. José Maria Gay

Richard Roberts, Nobel Prize in Medicine Introduced by Dr. José Manuel Calavia

Ada Yonath, Nobel Prize in Chemistry Introduced by Dr. José Luis Salido

Luis Alberto Lacalle, former president of Uruguay. Introduced by Dr. Xabier Añoveros

Debate: Public economy vs market economy

Participants:

Ahmad Ranema, lecturer at IESE;

Jaime Llopis, lecturer at IESE;

Joaquim Vila, lecturer at IESE;

Miguel Ángel Gallo, academician of the RAED and lecturer at IESE;

Ginés de Rus, professor at ULPGC;

Francisco Javier Llovera, professor at UPC.

Chaired by: Juan Francisco Corona, Director General of the Family Business Institute and academician of the RAED.
